<h2>Is an Equilateral Triangle a 30-60-90 Triangle?</h2>
<p>No, an equilateral triangle is not a 30-60-90 triangle. A 30-60-90 trian=
gle has angles of 30=C2=B0, 60=C2=B0, and 90=C2=B0, whereas an equilateral =
triangle has all angles equal to 60=C2=B0. Yet, a=20
30-60-90 triangle is noteworthy as well, because it corresponds to an isosc=
eles triangle, which has still a solid degree of symmetry.
