<h2>Scalene Triangle vs. Equilateral Triangle</h2>
<p>In what way does an scalene triangle differs from an <a href=3D"https://=
mathcracker.com/equilateral-triangle-calculator.php" data-google-interstiti=
al=3D"false">equilateral triangle</a>? A scalene triangle has all sides of =
different=20
    lengths, while an equilateral triangle has all sides equal. Here are so=
me key differences:</p>
<ul>
    <li><b>Scalene Triangle:</b> No equal sides or angles.</li>
    <li><b>Equilateral Triangle:</b> All sides and angles are equal.</li>
</ul>

<p>Notice that a triangle can be neither scalene nor equilateral, situation=
 that happens with an isosceles triangle.</p>

